node.text:
I present "ZERO LIMITS LAB".  My goal for this computer lab is not only meant for the youth in programs at Wohl Recreation Center, but for ALL members of the community to be able to have a resource to explore the limitless possibilities to impact their lives. This lab is meant to be just one of those resources. This lab can be used by the Center to: help students with homework assignments, empower people to search online for job applications, help to teach those in need of basic computer skills and résumé writing, provide an introduction to coding classes to the youth, help entrepreneurs access other resources to start new businesses, help people look for financial aid to further their education, help anyone research their personal interests and goals to overcome any obstacles to make them a reality, as I know, this list goes on and on... the possibilities have no limit!

Thank you to @microsoft , @beatsbydre , @neweracap , @jumpman23 and all of my family’s new friends who made this all possible.

node.text:
I present "ZERO LIMITS LAB".  My goal for this computer lab is not only meant for the youth in programs at Wohl Recreation Center, but for ALL members of the community to be able to have a resource to explore the limitless possibilities to impact their lives. This lab is meant to be just one of those resources. This lab can be used by the Center to: help students with homework assignments, empower people to search online for job applications, help to teach those in need of basic computer skills and résumé writing, provide an introduction to coding classes to the youth, help entrepreneurs access other resources to start new businesses, help people look for financial aid to further their education, help anyone research their personal interests and goals to overcome any obstacles to make them a reality, as I know, this list goes on and on... the possibilities have no limit!

Thank you to @microsoft , @beatsbydre , @neweracap , @jumpman23 and all of my family’s new friends who made this all possible.

node.text:
Everybody who knows me knows that my love for STL runs deep and I’m excited that I have the opportunity to make a difference.  My Foundation, The Jayson Tatum Foundation, is giving back in a major way and since we are all STL proud, we are looking for the whole city to help.

Wohls Community Center was like a second home to me and this is why it was important to open the FIRST EVER Computer Lab at Wohls.  The Computer Lab will have 12 Brand New Computers/Laptops and 2 printers.  We also want to make sure that the kids are ready for the school year by gifting them FREE book bags, Beats headphones, Celtics gear and school supplies. 

I’m incredibly appreciative of my amazing partners @microsoft , @neweracap , @jumpman23 , @beatsbydre & @celtics for their help and support, but we also need YOUR help.  Please help us by donating school supplies via the link in my bio and spread the word. We want to help as many kids as possible be ready for the school year.  STL where you at???

Please ensure the shipping address says “Jayson Tatum’s Foundation Gift Registry Address” when making the school supply donation.

Thank you for your support!
